- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper explicitly discusses the impact of control architecture on the performance of multiagent systems. 
- cs.GT (Game Theory) is also likely as the paper uses the metrics of price of anarchy and price of stability, which are commonly used in game theory. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the design of a communication protocol to improve system performance, which is a common topic in AI research. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of information constraints on emergent collective behavior, which is a topic relevant to social and information networks. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design of a distributed system with multiple agents and a system operator.
